abstract: |
  Ploidy is a structured-debate protocol between same-model LLM
  sessions with intentionally asymmetric context depths. It
  identifies two independent phenomena - context asymmetry
  (Event A) and stochastic variance (Event B) - and uses
  ploidy-level session scaling to distinguish them. The
  repository ships an MCP server implementation, an experiment
  runner supporting four model families, and a human-in-the-
  loop review capability.
